    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15e61ba1_ee3cf241",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_ios.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T01:17:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Don’t you want to ensure that Install was successful before anyone comes in here? Seems like you might want an InitializationStateDcheck now that you’ve got this DumpWithoutCrash public method.\n\nOnce you have an InitializationStateDcheck, you might be tempted to check it in HandleSignal and CatchMachException. The tricky part about that is that it won’t be set to valid until you’re done with Install, but if a signal occurs while you’re busy doing SetUpMachPort, or is raised essentially asynchronously by another thread (or by some prank pulled by something else on the system), it’ll trip the DCHECK when you hit HandleSignal. In fact, due to the fact that the Mach exception handler runs on another thread, it’s even possible for CatchMachException to run even before Install returns, so it could theoretically trip the DCHECK too. So I think that checking the InitializationStateDcheck in those codepaths is hazardous, and I wouldn’t recommend it (and, strictly speaking, it’s not necessary because they’re private and you’re not really trying to guard against your own logic errors with an InitializationStateDcheck as much as you’re trying to guard against other code not using your class correctly or forgetting to check return values.) But once you have the InitializationStateDcheck, it looks weird not to use it in places like HandleSignal and CatchMachException, so I’d say it’d be worth a comment at the tops of those functions explaining why you’re not doing it.",
      "revId": "df84b1a47454b4292d5b51ba3e3530b68b8e9da3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dbe8a84d_ec62349b",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_ios.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 47,
      "author": {
        "id": 1116294
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T20:33:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m confused, do you want InitializationStateDcheck elsewhere?  Or nowhere?",
      "parentUuid": "15e61ba1_ee3cf241",
      "revId": "df84b1a47454b4292d5b51ba3e3530b68b8e9da3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba080731_da53cff9",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_ios.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
