      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T21:41:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027m confused, do you want InitializationStateDcheck elsewhere?  Or nowhere?\n\nI want it to protect the public entry point(s): DumpWithoutCrash.\n\nYou can’t put it in the private entry points because they may be called essentially asynchronously with respect to Install returning.\n\nAlthough, if nothing Install does can fail, you can set the state to valid before installing the signal handler or Mach exception handler, and then you can check the InitializationStateDcheck in both of those handlers. But this isn’t really so important.",
      "parentUuid": "dbe8a84d_ec62349b",
      "revId": "df84b1a47454b4292d5b51ba3e3530b68b8e9da3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
