      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T21:41:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e No idea, but I\u0027m curious what happens when I start playing with iOS extensions.  What\u0027s your answer?\n\nI know the system doesn’t want you to make your own child processes, but I don’t know if anything on the system will make child processes for you. If it does, those children would inherit your task exception ports. Since you’re not really expecting to handle them, you’d reject them here.\n\nIs that why you put this here? I was just wondering if you had more inspiration for doing this, or if you actually saw a need.",
      "parentUuid": "1aef3765_ff53e65f",
      "revId": "df84b1a47454b4292d5b51ba3e3530b68b8e9da3",
