      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T01:17:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nope. Once we’re installed, we don’t want to uninstall.\n\nAll we want to do with original_handlers_ is forward an exception to a handler that used to be set, if there is one. We’d use UniversalExceptionRaise for this. But the flavor and behavior handling is a little tricky, so I’d suggest leaving this out for the time being (it was missing from your previous draft and I think that’s OK) so that we can focus on other things.\n\nA preview of correct UniversalExceptionRaise usage is in handler/mac/crash_report_exception_handler.cc, although you may get more value out of the comment that’s there than the actual implementation. The problem here is that I don’t think we have very strong assurance of the particular flavor and behavior that the previous handler wants, since the previous handler in this case is a debugger and may change. What we’ll wind up needing to do will look a lot like 10.15.0 xnu-6153.11.26/osfmk/kern/exception.c exception_deliver. That degenerates into a 6-headed monster, The UniversalExceptionRaise interface will make things a little easier.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 103,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 107,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "df84b1a47454b4292d5b51ba3e3530b68b8e9da3",
