      "writtenOn": "2020-04-23T01:17:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see why you split HandleSignal out, but it’s just to service DumpWithoutCrash (which doesn’t want reraise since there was no signal to begin with) separately. Ultimately, I don’t think we’ll be recycling the signal handler for this at all, I think we’ll just fire off a ProcessSnapshot right from there, without inventing a fake signal. So maybe we should just do that now, and re-merge this all into a single HandleSignal.\n\nOr, really, in the future we’ll wind up doing whatever we do when this turns into something that serializes instead of something that builds a forbidden snapshot. But I think that for this part of things, the structure will be the same. We won’t want to build a fake signal or a fake Mach exception at this level, we should just write the code to treat all three sources as equal peers: signals, Mach exceptions, and direct requests from the program (DumpWithoutCrash).",
